f-134_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">1 hour / 1 day / 1 week / 1 month moving averages</span></span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-135_"><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-136_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-138_">Radon Measurement Range</span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-139_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-141_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">0.2 ~ 99.9 pCi/L (7~3,700Bq/m³)</span></span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-142_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-144_">Radon Alarm</span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-145_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-147_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Integrated audio alarm (configurable to set radon level)</span></span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-148_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-150_">Radon Level Visual Indicator</span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-151_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-153_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">LED display</span></span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-154_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-156_">Power Supply</span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-157_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-159_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">5V, 1A, Extend DC adapter</span></span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-160_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-162_">Weight</span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-163_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-165_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">0.341 lb (155 g)</span></span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-166_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-168_">Operating Temp Range</span></p><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-169_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-171_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">32°F~104°F (0~40°C)</span></span></p></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-expandable="true" style="display:none" data-pf-type="TabsContent" class="sc-fmciRz fEcqOy pf-172_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-173_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-175_">Frequently Asked Questions</span></h3><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-176_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-177_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-dkYRCH hYpqjU pf-178_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-179_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-181_">What is the service life of the EcoBlu?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-182_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-184_">EcoBlu is expected to have a service life of 5 years but this depends on usage conditions, wear and tear, etc.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-185_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-187_">What does the EcoBlu package come with?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-188_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-190_">EcoBlu package includes the EcoBlu unit along with a power adapter.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-191_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-193_">What is the operating temperature range of EcoBlu?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-194_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-196_">The operating temperature range of RadonEye is 32°F ~ 104°F  and Relative Humidity &lt; 80%.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-197_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-199_">Where should I place the device?&nbsp;</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-200_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-202_">Place EcoBlu at least 20 inches (50 cm) above the floor and from the wall. Do not place EcoBlu close to open windows or vents and keep it away from high heat and high humidity. Install at least 24 inches (61 cm) away from Wi-Fi routers and hotspot devices that may affect electromagnetic interference (EMI) on your device.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-203_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-205_">How often does the device need to be calibrated?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-206_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-208_">The calibration is not required by law for consumer devices, but our manufacturer initially calibrated EcoBlu. Also, EcoBlu is expected to have a service life of 5 years but this depends on usage conditions, wear tear, etc.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-209_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-211_">How to factory reset the device?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-212_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-214_">Press the M button on the back of the device for 10 seconds to enter the factory reset mode. A factory reset will erase data from your device and reset device settings to its original system state.&nbsp;</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-215_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-217_">I suddenly see high radon reading, what should I do?&nbsp;</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-218_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-220_">Please make sure if you Install the device at least 24 inches (61 cm) away from Wi-Fi routers and hotspot devices that may affect electromagnetic interference (EMI) on your device. If this is not the case, you may want to check if your device works well by running the test outside, for example, on the patio or backyard. Place your device avoiding direct sunlight and soil blown in the wind, when it’s not rainy or stormy. Also, place it 20 inches away from the floor or ground and the walls. You must keep it running for over an hour. If radon levels go over 1pCi/L, your device could be defective. Please contact the Ecosense support team.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-221_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-223_">Is EcoBlu certified?&nbsp;</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-224_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-226_">No, EcoBlu is not certified and the certification is not required by law for consumer devices.&nbsp;</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-227_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-229_">Does this monitor have an audible alarm if the radon levels are high?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-230_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-232_">Yes, EcoBlu has an audio alarm and you can adjust the settings. You can turn on or off the alarm by clicking the S button on the back of the device. Press the S button for 3 seconds to enter the setting mode, then click the S button again to select alarm level. After selecting the alarm level setting, click the M button to select the desired alarm level. Press the S button for 3 seconds to complete the setting.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-233_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-235_">I see various radon levels, what should I do?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-236_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-238_">Radon levels tend to fluctuate (changes in weather, wind from open windows, humidity, etc.), so the recommended action is to monitor the radon level continuously for at least 90 days. This will give you the most accurate assessment of the radon levels in your home. Please refer to the EPA testing guidelines. Radon measurement equipment is required to be located 20 inches away from the floor. It is necessary to install the equipment on a chair or table made of a material other than stone or soil and to keep it away from the wall or window as well.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-239_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-241_">Radon level fluctuates throughout the day. Does this monitor show the historic hour by hour readings?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-242_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-244_">Device updates radon reading every 10 minutes on R mode. Also provide an average of daily, weekly, monthly and an average of all previous measurement time.&nbsp;</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-245_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-247_">What are considered safe ranges for radon?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-248_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-250_">EPA recommends homes be fixed if the radon level is 4 pCi/L (picocuries per liter) or more. Because there is no known safe level of exposure to radon, EPA also recommends that Americans consider fixing their home for radon levels between 2 pCi/L and 4 pCi/L.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-251_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-253_">How long is the data stored for long-term monitoring mode?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-254_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-256_">The memory in EcoBlu will hold a maximum of 1 year of radon readings. After 1 year, the oldest data will be deleted.&nbsp;</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-257_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-259_">What is the difference between each mode?</span></h3><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-260_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jHkVzv VcvBI pf-261_ pf-text-2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-263_">R (Real-time monitoring mode):<br>Default mode when the device is first powered on and radon reading updates every 10 minutes with an hourly moving average. If the device powers off, reading will be automatically reset.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jHkVzv VcvBI pf-264_ pf-text-2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-266_">D (Daily monitoring mode):<br>Radon reading updates every hour with the last 24 hours of moving average. First data is available after 24 hours of data points have been collected. If the device powers off, reading will be automatically reset.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jHkVzv VcvBI pf-267_ pf-text-2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-269_">W (Weekly monitoring mode):<br>Radon reading updates every 24 hours with the last 7 days of moving average. First data is available after 7 days of data points have been collected. If the device powers off, reading will be automatically reset.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jHkVzv VcvBI pf-270_ pf-text-2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-272_">M (Monthly monitoring mode):<br>Radon reading updates every 24 hours with the last 30 days of moving average. First data is available after 30 days of data points have been collected. If the device powers off, reading will be automatically reset.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-jHkVzv VcvBI pf-273_ pf-text-2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-275_">L (Long-term monitoring mode):<br>Radon reading updates every 24 hours with total days averaged since monitoring began. First data is available after 24 hours of data points have been collected. If the device powers off and on, the last reading will be displayed and radon readings will not be deleted until the device is manually reset.</span></li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-276_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-278_">What is the return and refund policy?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-279_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-281_">We offer returns and refunds within 30 days of the original purchase date. You will be responsible for paying the postage/shipping fees for returning your device. If the device is determined to be defective, you will receive a full refund, and the return shipping fees will be refunded to you by Ecosense.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-282_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-284_">Am I going to lose data if a power outage happens?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-285_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-287_">Readings are automatically reset in real-time(R), weekly(W) and monthly(M) mode when the device is powered off. However, in long-term monitoring mode, the last reading will be displayed and radon readings will not be deleted until the device is manually reset.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-288_ pf-heading-2-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-290_">What happens to saved data if I decide to move the device to another room?</span></h3><p class="sc-jWUzzU cKWSZG pf-291_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-293_">When you move the device and start measuring in a different location, the device resets in R, W, and M modes, and you can get new readings. However, since data is continuously saved in long-term monitoring mode, it is recommended to reset the data before starting measurements after moving to another location.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-294_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-295_"><a href="/products/ecoblu" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-nVkyK egIfgS pf-296_ pf-button-4"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-298_">Buy Now</span></a><a href="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0106/9911/2511/files/Final_Brochure_EcoBlu_V2.0_compressed.pdf?v=1667949627" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-nVkyK egIfgS pf-299_ pf-button-4"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-301_">EcoBlu Product Brochure</span></a><a href="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0106/9911/2511/files/EB100W-Userguide-multil.pdf" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-nVkyK egIfgS pf-302_ pf-button-4"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eXlEPa iXKoRS pf-304_">EcoBlu User Guide</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><script>
